# Financial Calculation Standards

## Numeric Precision
- Use `number` for all financial values — avoid string concatenation for math
- Round for display only: `(v * 100).toFixed(1) + '%'`
- Percentages stored as decimals: 0.05 = 5%, not 5

## Return Calculations
```typescript
// ✅ Correct: (end - start) / start
const returnPct = (valueNow - valueStart) / valueStart;

// ❌ Wrong: (end - start) / end
```

## Drawdown
- Drawdown = (peak - current) / peak
- Always non-negative in display; store as positive for maxDrawdown

## Staleness
- Never execute trades on `isStale: true` data when age > 2× threshold
- Flag but serve stale data — don't block UI

## Edge Cases
- Division: check denominator > 0 before dividing
- Empty arrays: return 0 or [] for metrics, never NaN
- Starting capital: PAPER_CONFIG.startingCapital = 1_000_000
